00:00:05.440 --> 00:00:11.360
What do sunglasses sold by Chanel, Bulgary,
Dolce and Gabbana, versace, Tiffany, Ray Ban,

00:00:11.360 --> 00:00:17.040
Oakley, Prada, Burberry and Ralph Lauren have
in common? Besides being frighteningly expensive,

00:00:17.050 --> 00:00:21.440
they are all made and owned by one company.
Luxottica.

00:00:21.440 --> 00:00:26.300
Ray Ban came out with their first pair of
sunglasses back in the 1930's in the form

00:00:26.300 --> 00:00:31.179
of aviation sunglasses which were specially
designed for the United States Air force.

00:00:31.179 --> 00:00:36.410
These Anti- glare sunglasses were crafted
to cut light at high altitudes without obstructing

00:00:36.410 --> 00:00:42.350
vision. These sunglasses were remodeled in
1937 with a metal frame today popularly known

00:00:42.350 --> 00:00:46.820
as the Aviators.
In 1984 Oakley released their first sports

00:00:46.820 --> 00:00:53.150
oriented sunglasses called the Factory Pilot
eye shades followed by Oakley Frogskin. The

00:00:53.150 --> 00:00:58.870
company raised 230 million dollars by 1985.
Another milestone worth mentioning is the

00:00:58.870 --> 00:01:04.670
Oakley M frame sunglasses which are included
as part of the US army's authorized uniform.

00:01:04.670 --> 00:01:10.039
So let us now tell you why sunglasses are
so expensive. This probably has something

00:01:10.039 --> 00:01:15.270
to do with the illusion of choice and the
fact that one company owns over 80% of the

00:01:15.270 --> 00:01:22.840
planet's major eyewear brands. In 1961 Luxottica
started off in a tool shop in Algodo, Italy.

00:01:22.840 --> 00:01:28.009
Today, Luxottica is known for manufacturing
more than 6 and a half crore pairs of sunglasses

00:01:28.009 --> 00:01:33.249
every year.
In 1980s Luxottica started buying every sunglasses

00:01:33.249 --> 00:01:37.709
company it could get its hands on along with
convincing every fashion designer into letting

00:01:37.709 --> 00:01:42.969
them make their sunglasses line. So if you're
wearing high end Tifanny sunglasses or last

00:01:42.969 --> 00:01:48.029
year's stock clearance from Sunglass Hut,
well you're wearing Luxottica.

00:01:48.029 --> 00:01:51.749
This is the reason why they can charge you
a massive sum of money for a piece of plastic

00:01:51.749 --> 00:01:57.560
with two hinges. Because most of their competition
isn't inexpensive unbranded products, its

00:01:57.560 --> 00:02:03.229
other brands they own. Luxottica is using
it's near monopolistic control of sunglasses

00:02:03.229 --> 00:02:08.349
to keep the prices artificially high
Luxottica's bestselling sunglasses are none

